.ui.inverted.vertical.center.aligned.segment
  .ui.container.fluid
    .ui.huge.borderless.menu.inverted.header
      .ui.container
        = link_to root_path, class: 'item header' do
          PetNoter
        .right.menu
        - if user_signed_in?
          = link_to pets_find_path do
            .ui.inverted.button.green Find an owner
          = link_to pets_path do
            .ui.inverted.button.violet Your pets
          = link_to edit_user_registration_path do
            .ui.inverted.button Settings
          = link_to destroy_user_session_path, method: :delete do
            .ui.inverted.button.red Sign out
        - else
          = link_to pets_find_path do
            .ui.item.inverted.button.green Find an owner
          = link_to new_user_session_path do
            .ui.item.inverted.button.blue Login
  .ui.text.container
    %h1.ui.inverted.header
      PetList
    %h2
      Pakistan's
      %strong only public
      pet microchip database
    = form_tag(new_registration_path(:user), method: :get, class: 'ui action input') do
      = text_field_tag(:chip_number, nil, {placeholder: 'Chip Number', class: 'ui'})
      = button_tag(:register, class: 'ui huge primary button') do
        Register
        %i.right.arrow.icon
  .ui.container.top.space
    .ui.three.column.stackable.grid.centered
      .ui.column.center.aligned
        .ui.segment.inverted.violet.facts
          .ui.h2.header What is a microchip implant for pets?
          A microchip is a implant is a small — the size of a rice grain — permanent electronic identification device that's injected just under the skin behind your pet's neck.
      .ui.column.center.aligned
        .ui.segment.inverted.violet.facts
          .ui.h2.header Is it safe? Where can I get it?
          Yes! The chip itself is encased in sterile glass, and the procedure is as quick and painless as an injection. For more information, talk to your existing vet!
      .ui.column.center.aligned
        .ui.segment.inverted.violet.facts
          .ui.h2.header How does registration work?
          Each microchip has a unique ID that can be registered to your name here at PetList, permantly linking you to your pet. Lost pets can be reunited with their owners here.
.ui.inverted.vertical.footer.segment
  .ui.container
    .ui.stackable.inverted.divided.equal.height.stackable.grid
      .three.wide.column
